## 0. Purpose & scope

Extract the **post-issuance capital structure snapshot** from ASX Appendix 2A PDFs. The only part of the document that matters for valuation is **Part 4 — Issued capital following quotation** (always the last page). Everything before it (entity header, issuance event details, previous 3B reference, distribution schedule) is context that the parser deliberately ignores.

**This parser produces exactly three things:**

1. `shares_basic` — total quoted ordinary shares on issue after this application (from Part 4.1)
2. `unquoted_instruments[]` — structured list of every option / convertible note / performance right (from Part 4.2) with face count, strike, expiry
3. `shares_fd_naive` — `shares_basic + sum(unquoted_instruments.total_on_issue)` as a reconciled upper bound

Nothing else. If the dashboard ever needs the issue price of the specific tranche or the previous 3B link, that is a separate parser or a direct ASX-API lookup — not this parser's job.

